It is a part of Rich Township District 227, which also includes Rich East High School and Rich South High School.
High School District #227 serves the residents of Country Club Hills, Matteson, Olympia Fields, Park Forest, Richton Park, a small section of Chicago Heights and adjoining rural areas in South Cook County.
Rich Central High School has 21 athletic teams, of 10 boys and 11 girls teams, which play in the South Inter-Conference Association and the Illinois High School Association.
